      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">詩經·小雅·節南山之什·002.2</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">正月.2</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>謂山蓋卑，為岡為陵。民之訛言，寧莫之懲！
召彼故老，訊之占夢。具曰予聖，誰知烏之雌雄？</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>If one say of a hill that it is low,
There are its ridges and its large masses.
The false calumnies of the people,—
How
is it that you do not repress them?
You call those experienced ancients,
You consult the diviner of dreams.
They all say, 'We are very wise,
But who can distinguish the male and female crow?'</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="shijing__xiaoya-jienanshan-002__003__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sbe-v3-1879">
